title: Pleasant Hill ends Helias’ volleyball season
text:
Pleasant Hill ends Helias’ volleyball season Sunday, October 25, 2015 
AURORA, Mo. — The Helias Lady Crusaders dropped a two-game decision to Pleasant Hill in the sectional round of the Class 3 state volleyball tournament Saturday. 
Pleasant Hill won 25-22, 25-20. 
Ashley Dudenhoeffer had 23 assists, nine digs and five service points for the Lady Crusaders. Ellie Rockers led with six kills, while Hannah Borcelt and Erin Wyrick had five each and Suzie Kuensting had four. Blake Berhorst totaled five points and five digs. 
Helias, the defending Class 3 state champion, ends the season at 30-4-1. 
Pleasant Hill defeated Logan-Rogersville 25-21, 25-18 to advance to the Final Four. ﻿
